  "text": "The 'acks' producer configuration propagates through the Kafka codebase in the following chain:\n\n1. **Definition and Validation (Client-Side)**:\n   - ProducerConfig.java (line 123): Defines the ACKS_CONFIG constant as \"acks\"\n   - ProducerConfig.java (line 579-596): Reads and validates the acks configuration, converting string values (\"0\", \"1\", \"all\") to short values (0, 1, -1). The parseAcks() method (line 639-643) handles the conversion and validation.\n\n2. **Producer Initialization (Client-Side)**:\n   - KafkaProducer.java (line 526): Extracts the acks configuration value and passes it to the Sender class constructor (line 533)\n\n3. **Encoding into Protocol (Client-Side)**:\n   - Sender.java (line 99): Stores the acks value as a field in the Sender class\n   - Sender.java (line 899): Sets the acks value into the ProduceRequestData via setAcks(acks)\n   - ProduceRequest.json (line 55): Defines the Acks field schema as int16 in the protocol message definition\n   - ProduceRequest.java (line 91-104): Contains the acks field with getter method (line 193-194)\n   - Sender.java (line 912): Uses acks != 0 to determine if the request should await a response\n\n4. **Broker-Side Request Handling**:\n   - KafkaApis.scala (line 388-544): handleProduceRequest() extracts the acks value from the ProduceRequest (line 486, 499) and passes it to ReplicaManager.handleProduceAppend() as requiredAcks (line 537)\n   - The acks value determines:\n     - Whether request throttling quota is applied (line 486: skipped if acks==0)\n     - Whether to send a response immediately (line 499: immediate response if acks==0)\n\n5. **Broker-Side Replication Logic**:\n   - ReplicaManager.scala (line 731-815): handleProduceAppend() receives the requiredAcks and passes it to appendRecords()\n   - ReplicaManager.scala (line 674-712): appendRecords() validates requiredAcks with isValidRequiredAcks() (line 683-686) and passes it to appendRecordsToLeader() and maybeAddDelayedProduce()\n   - ReplicaManager.scala (line 1363-1365): isValidRequiredAcks() only accepts -1, 1, or 0 as valid values\n   - ReplicaManager.scala (line 1370-1409): appendToLocalLog() passes requiredAcks to partition.appendRecordsToLeader() (line 1408)\n\n6. **Partition-Level Write Acknowledgment**:\n   - Partition.scala (line 1361-1388): appendRecordsToLeader() uses requiredAcks to validate write conditions:\n     - When requiredAcks == -1, it checks that in-sync replica (ISR) size meets minIsr requirement (line 1370)\n     - Throws NotEnoughReplicasException if ISR is too small for acks=all\n\n7. **Delayed Response Handling**:\n   - ReplicaManager.scala (line 908-933): maybeAddDelayedProduce() uses requiredAcks to determine response timing:\n     - line 1355-1361: delayedProduceRequestRequired() returns true only when requiredAcks == -1 (line 1358), causing a DelayedProduce to wait for all ISR replicas\n     - line 916-932: If delayed produce is not required, the response is sent immediately; otherwise a DelayedProduce is created\n   - DelayedProduce.scala (line 57+): The DelayedProduce class waits for acks satisfaction before allowing the response to be sent\n\nIn summary, the acks configuration controls: (1) at the client, when to expect a response; (2) at the broker, whether to validate ISR size, apply throttling, and whether to delay the response until all replicas acknowledge the write."
